OL,3,CPolar bears face starvation risk in
OL,4,Clonger ice-free periods in Arctic
OL,6,FThe scientists, from Washington State
OL,7,FUniversity and US Geological Survey,
OL,8,Fwarned the bears, particularly
OL,9,Fyoungsters, were at increased risk of
OL,10,Fstarvation with the greater amount of
OL,11,Ftime they had to spend on land.
OL,13,FThe ice-free period in Hudson Bay has
OL,14,Fincreased by three weeks from 1975 to
OL,15,F2015, reducing the amount of time
OL,16,Fpolar bears can spend on the ice,
OL,17,Fwhere they catch and eat seals to
OL,18,Fbolster their energy reserves.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/9
