OL,3,CPolar bears face starvation risk in
OL,4,Clonger ice-free periods in Arctic
OL,6,FThe assessments revealed they had a
OL,7,Fwide range of strategies on land, from
OL,8,Fhibernation-like resting to conserve
OL,9,Fenergy, to actively foraging for food
OL,10,Fon land and even swimming tens of
OL,11,Fkilometres.
OL,13,FBears consumed berries, vegetation,
OL,14,Fbirds, bones, antlers, seal and beluga
OL,15,Fwhale.
OL,17,FThere was very little benefit from
OL,18,Fforaging, as 19 of the 20 animals lost
OL,19,Fweight during the period, dropping an
OL,20,Faverage of 1kg (2.2lbs) a day.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/9
