OL,6,FHe added: "Our results suggest that
OL,7,Fpolar bears cannot alter their
OL,8,Fbehaviour or energetics in ways that
OL,9,Fcan prevent weight loss when summering
OL,10,Fon land and that, in most cases, the
OL,11,Fresources available on land are
OL,12,Finsufficient to counteract weight
OL,13,Floss."
OL,15,FCharles Robbins, director of the
OL,16,FWashington State University Bear
OL,17,FCentre and co-author of the study,
OL,18,Fsaid neither strategy of resting to
OL,19,Fconserve energy or foraging would
OL,20,Fallow polar bears to exist on land
OL,21,Fbeyond a certain amount of time.
